raw._content: 030304-F-0000X-001.File Photo.  U.S. Air Force RC-135 Rivet Joint. The RC-135 is a reconnaissance aircraft supporting theater and national level consumers with near real time on-scene intelligence collection, analysis and dissemination capabilities.  On March 2, 2003, four North Korean fighter jets intercepted a U.S. Air Force plane in international airspace over the Sea of Japan.  Aircraft Statistics: Primary Function:  Reconnaissance.  Contractor.  Boeing Aerospace Co. and E-Systems.  Speed:  More than 500 mph.  Dimensions:  Wingspan 130 ft. 10 in., length 145 ft. 6 in., height 41 ft. 4 in.  Range:  More than 11 hours without refueling.  Crew:  Up to 32.  U.S. Air Force photo courtesy Air Force Link.  (RELEASED)  For more information go to the U.S. Air Force Fact File at http://www.af.mil/news/factsheets/RC_135V_W_Rivet_Joint.html.
